=====================================
 
 
$terraform init 
1) Initializes a Terraform working directory
2) Downloads required provider plugins (AWS, Azure, GCP, etc
Downloads providers
Stores them in .terraform/
Creates .terraform.lock.hcl
3) Sets up backend configuration for state storage
4) Installs modules referenced in your configuration
	
//.terraform.lock.hcl -Locks provider versions || (Dependency lock file for provider versions. It ensures consistent, reproducible builds across machines and CI pipelines.)
//terraform.tfstate - Tracks infrastructure state ||  It stores the mapping between: 1)Terraform configuration 2)Real-world infrastructure resources.
>Terraform does not query cloud providers for everything every time.Instead, it relies on this state file.


$ terraform validate  //Checks if your Terraform configuration files are syntactically valid
$ terraform fmt    //Format code 
$ terraform plan  // See execution plan
$ terraform plan -out=helloPlan01.plan  //To save the plan to a file
$ terraform apply helloplan01.plan     //To apply the plan
$ terraform show      //to list the current applied state.
$ terraform apply    //Apply changes
$ terraform destroy  // 
$ terraform state list //To list the applied 

